# AGENTS.md

Repository conventions for all AI coding agents (Claude Code, Cursor, Copilot, Windsurf, etc.).

## Branch Strategy

- **`main`** — production. Never commit or push directly.
- **`development`** — preview/staging. Never push directly — always via PR.
- **`feature/*`** — short-lived. Branch from `development`, PR back to `development`. Delete after merge.

```
feature/* → development → main
```

## Agent Workflow

This project uses agentgate for agent workflow skills. Skills are available as:

- **Claude Code:** `/start`, `/ship`, `/review`, `/version`, `/release` slash commands
- **Cursor:** `@start`, `@ship`, etc. in Agent mode

### Quick reference

| Skill | When to use |
|---|---|
| `/start [description]` | Begin a new feature or bugfix |
| `/start [issue-number]` | Resume work on an existing GitHub Issue |
| `/ship` | Type-check, commit, open PR, review, merge to `development` |
| `/review [pr-number]` | Standalone code review (defaults to current branch's PR) |
| `/version` | Bump version, tag, push — run before deploying to preview |
| `/release` | Promote `development` to `main`, close issues, prep for production deploy |

## What Agents Must Never Do

- Push directly to `main` or `development`
- Merge PRs targeting `main` (use `/release` instead)
- Run destructive commands (drop DB, clear prod data) without explicit human instruction
- Commit `.env` files, secrets, or build artifacts

